                </FooterDetails>
                <Header>History</Header>
                <Paragraph>A Director of National Intelligence for coordinating the overall intelligence effort is an idea that predates the establishment of the ODNI by five decades. The attacks of September 11, 2001, against the World Trade Center and the subsequent report by the National Commission on Terrorist Attacks Upon the United States (better known as the 9/11 Commission) increased the momentum for major intelligence reform.  To learn more of the story, visit the "History" web page.</Paragraph>
